    money_burned: 1200000000,
    founded_year: 2016,
    died_year: 2021,
    country: "China",
    founder_count: 1,
    employee_count: 0,
    lessons_learned: ["Hardware startups cannot iterate their way to product-market fit—the cost of each iteration in automotive is $100M+ and 18+ months. Your first production design must be 90% right, which means extensive virtual validation and ruthless feature prioritization. Byton's signature 48-inch screen should have been a Phase 2 feature after proving they could manufacture a simpler vehicle profitably.","In capital-intensive businesses, your funding strategy IS your product strategy. Byton needed $3-5B committed upfront or a radically different approach (contract manufacturing, platform licensing, or starting with commercial fleets). Raising in tranches with milestone gates creates a doom loop in hardware: delays are inevitable, missed milestones block funding, lack of funding causes more delays. Structure capital for reality, not optimism.","Supplier relationships in automotive are based on volume commitments and payment terms that startups cannot meet. Byton's custom display required a supplier to invest $50M+ in tooling with no guarantee of orders. The lesson: design around existing supply chains for your first product, or secure a strategic partner who will absorb supplier risk (like Magna or Foxconn as a true manufacturing partner, not just investor).","Attempting vertical integration (building your own factory) while simultaneously developing a complex product splits focus and multiplies capital requirements. Tesla could do this because Elon raised unlimited capital and had a simpler initial product (Roadster on Lotus platform). Startups should use contract manufacturers (like Magna Steyr) for first 50K units to preserve capital and prove demand before committing to fixed assets.","Technology differentiation must solve a customer problem, not just showcase capability. The 48-inch screen was engineering theater—impressive but not tied to a specific job-to-be-done that justified the cost and complexity. Contrast with Tesla's OTA updates (solved a real problem: recalls) or Rivian's gear tunnel (solved adventure storage). If your signature feature requires explaining why it matters, it's probably not the right first feature."],
