    died_year: 2025,
    country: "USA",
    founder_count: 1,
    employee_count: 0,
    lessons_learned: ["Debt financing for growth-stage consumer businesses is a death trap—equity dilution is painful but bankruptcy is fatal. Byju's $1.2B Term Loan B created fixed obligations that couldn't flex when market conditions changed, while equity would have provided breathing room.","Acquisition-led growth strategies fail without ruthless integration discipline. Byju's bought Epic and others but never unified them into a coherent product, creating cost bloat and strategic confusion. Modern founders should build > buy, or only acquire for specific capabilities with clear integration plans.","Premium pricing in edtech requires exceptional product quality and outcomes proof. Byju's charged $1000+ annually but couldn't demonstrate learning gains superior to free alternatives like Khan Academy, making the value proposition untenable for most families.","High-touch sales models (inside sales teams cold-calling parents) don't scale in modern consumer edtech. CAC of $300-500 per customer requires multi-year retention at premium pricing—a nearly impossible combination. Product-led growth with freemium models is the only sustainable path.","International expansion requires deep local market understanding. Byju's tried to transplant an Indian model (aggressive sales, premium pricing, parent anxiety-driven marketing) to the US market where parents are more skeptical and alternatives are abundant. Cultural product-market fit matters as much as functional fit.","The edtech market punishes mediocre engagement ruthlessly. If kids don't love using the product daily, churn is inevitable regardless of parent intentions. Byju's focused on sales and marketing over product excellence, a fatal prioritization error.","AI tutoring is now technically and economically viable in ways impossible in 2021. GPT-4 and Claude can provide personalized explanations, adaptive problem generation, and Socratic dialogue at near-zero marginal cost—the core value prop Byju's tried to deliver through expensive human infrastructure.","School district B2B channels are more defensible than direct-to-consumer in edtech. Byju's focused on consumer subscriptions, but districts provide larger contracts, longer sales cycles with higher retention, and validation that drives consumer adoption. Modern edtech should pursue dual-channel strategies.","Edtech requires continuous content investment that many founders underestimate. Curriculum becomes outdated, standards change, and engagement requires fresh material. This 'content debt' must be factored into unit economics from day one—AI content generation now makes this manageable."],
